1 Sec. 10. (a) A bonded certificate of title is valid for:
2 (1) three (3) years for a vintage motor vehicle that has a
3 vehicle identification number; or
4 (2) five (5) years for a vintage motor vehicle that has a special
5 identification number.
6 (b) If there are no claims made against the bonded title within
7 the time frames described in subsection (a), the bonded certificate
8 of title becomes a certificate of title under IC 9-17-2.
9 Sec. 11. (a) A person who knowingly or intentionally provides
10 false information to receive a bonded certificate of title commits
11 fraud involving a bonded certificate of title, a Level 6 felony.
12 (b) In addition to the penalties described in IC 35-50-2-7(b), a
13 person who is convicted of a Level 6 felony under this section shall
14 have the person's bonded certificate of title invalidated.
15 Sec. 12. The bureau shall allow the:
16 (1) application for; and
17 (2) processing of:
18 bonded certificates of title to occur at license branches.
